<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-631-318  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 631 318.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Sept 11 1989 v23 n37 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Wang cuts 1,000, with more likely. (layoffs at Wang LaboratoriesInc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Johnson, Maryfran.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Wang Laboratories Inc has laid off at least 1,000 employees, withhundreds more jobs expected to be cut over a three-week period inSep 1989.andP;  The moves marked the first sweep of the company'saccelerated restructuring and cost-cutting campaign, which willreduce the firm's employee count by at least 3,000 and possibly asmany as 7,000.andP;  The company will announce the official total atthe end of September.andP;  Analysts hailed the layoffs as necessaryand long overdue, noting that Wang had become bloated during itsyears of rapid growth.andP;  Short-term costs of the work forcereductions will be high despite the long-term savings, incurringsuch costs as vacation and severance pay and outplacement servicesfor some employees.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Wang Laboratories Inc. (layoffs).andO;Ticker:    WANC.andO;Topic:     Computer industryLayoffCost ReductionPersonnel Management.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>